caption: Located on the convergence of two main roads, one will find a bronze naked curvy lady created by  Antoniucci Volti in 1992, which adds to the beauty of the area.
Impressive when people do not use it to dump their garbage.
Spectacular bronze sculpture, which adapts to the environment where it is located, forming part of the urban furniture.

Harmony is a work of the French sculptor Antoniucci Volti (1915-1989). Installed since 1992 on Place Theodor-Herzl, at the corner of rue de Turbigo and rue Réaumur, Paris (3rd). Monumental bronze sculpture 2.50 m long representing a female character, lying down and sleeping. The sculpture rests on a cylindrical pedestal. On its edge, it bears the name of the work and the author, as well as his dates of birth and death.
